# Marker file read by scripts/mirror-images.py.
#
# When this file is present in a containers/<name>/ directory, the mirror
# script uses the repository root as the `docker buildx build` context
# instead of the per-tool directory, and passes
# `-f containers/<name>/Dockerfile` explicitly.
#
# The metadata-writer image needs the repo root as context so it can
# COPY `pricing/healthomics-ap-southeast-1.json` into the image at build
# time (Design D9, Requirement 17.10).
